### [META]
id: "test-vectors"
level: 2
parent: "../0.1-AI-MANIFEST.a2ml"

### [AI_MANIFEST]
description: |
  Committed, cross-implementation test vectors — the machine-checkable freeze
  for wire formats that estate sibling apps pin against.

  Files:
    ble-spa-v1.json — BLE presence wire format v1 (ADR-0015). Regenerated by
      `mix burble.gen_ble_vectors` from Burble.Presence.BleSpa; verified in CI
      by server/test/burble/presence/ble_spa_vectors_test.exs. Consumers
      (e.g. neurophone) validate their decoders against the same bytes.

  Any drift in these bytes is a wire break: it requires a superseding ADR, a
  major bump of server/mix.exs @version, and a CHANGELOG "Protocol" entry.
